task.summary: Re-implemented my views using built-in generic views.
Adjusted the post signature upon super-ing it to match the initial `post` signature in `post` definition
Added the urls and url patterns
Adjusted the required imports for the urls.py file.

Created the `users` app, with `register`, `login` and `logout` endpoints. Implemented custom `Token authentication` for the users. Actually, Chris did that. Implemented a custom permission `IsOwner` to make sure `ContactOwners` can only `CRUD` their contacts. Created a custom `User` model `ContactOwner` and a corresponding custom manager `ContactOwnerManager`. And so on.
I also tried to separate `Registration` from `Login` in `php-users`. As much as it works, it is not exactly convenient for the CLIENT and means more request/response round trips.
